        </section>
        <section>
            <title>Sources for Large Pieces of <text
                    conref="termsUsed.dita#reusableTerms/termMatboardCAP"/></title>
            <p>Consider buying a large piece of <text
                    conref="termsUsed.dita#reusableTerms/termMatboard"/> when you need a
                non-standard size, when you cannot locate the precut size you need, or when you
                simply prefer to make your own mats for a number of reasons. Then you will cut it to
                the size you need.</p>
            <p>Acid-free <text conref="termsUsed.dita#reusableTerms/termMatboard"/> is recommended
                to reduce fading over time.</p>
            <p>Many art supply stores and craft stores carry <text
                    conref="termsUsed.dita#reusableTerms/termMatboard"/>. Here are some online
                sources for buying large sizes of <text
                    conref="termsUsed.dita#reusableTerms/termMatboard"/>:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Off-white color: Dick Blick, Crescent RagMat 32"x40" Palm Beach White, available
                    online at: <xref href="https://www.dickblick.com/items/13007-1396/"
                        format="html" scope="external"/></li>
                <li>Other colors: <xref
                        href="https://www.dickblick.com/products/crescent-ragmat-matboard/"
                        format="html" scope="external"/></li>
                <li>A different source for white and off-white colors: <xref
                        href="https://framing4yourself.com/shop/products/decorative-mat-board-whites-and-whites/palm-beach-white-987/"
                        format="html" scope="external"/></li>
            </ul>
        </section>
